sql:
SELECT model_name
FROM models
ORDER BY created_at DESC, model_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Machine learning models are typically evaluated on multiple experiments to ensure robustness and reliability; 
- Test average precision is a measure of a model's performance, indicating the proportion of true positives among all predicted positive instances; 
- Experiment IDs and model names serve as identifiers to organize and compare experiments and models; 
- Average test average precision provides a summary of model performance across experiments, helping in comparing models and identifying top-performing ones.

